    "description": [
        {
            "text": "The unit $\\{Volt Per Meter (V/m)}$ is a unit in the category of Electric field strength. \n  It is also known as volts per meter, volt/meter, volt/metre, volt per metre, volts per metre. \n  This unit is commonly used in the SI unit system. \n  $\\{Volt Per Meter}$ has a dimension of $MLT^{-3}I^{-1}$ where $M$ is mass, $L$ is length, $T$ is time, and $I$ is electric current. \n  This unit is the standard SI unit in this category.",
            "lang": "en"
        }
    ],
